ed clinical hours."}]]}]]}],["$","div","04",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"04"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Front desk staff manage in-person and virtual simultaneously without enough support"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"A single front desk team managing in-person check-in, phone calls, scheduling, and virtual care coordination simultaneously is being asked to do the work of two different operational models at the same time. Something always falls behind — usually the less visible virtual tasks."}]]}]]}],["$","div","05",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"05"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Virtual visit follow-up is inconsistent"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"After-visit summaries, follow-up care reminders, referral coordination, and prescription confirmations require the same follow-through as in-person visits — but they are easier to defer when the patient was never physically in the building. Virtual follow-up gets less attention than it needs."}]]}]]}],["$","div","06",{"className":"pain-item","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"pain-num","children":"06"}],["$","div",null,{"children":[["$","h4",null,{"children":"Generic VA services do not understand healthcare workflow"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"A virtual assistant who does not understand clinical context, payer requirements, prior authorization processes, or HIPAA-compliant communication creates as many problems as they solve. Healthcare virtual support requires healthcare-specific knowledge — not general administrative experience."}]]}]]}]]}]]}]}],"$undefined",["$","section",null,{"className":"block block--ink","id":"solution","children":["$","div",null,{"className":"container","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"block-head fade-in","children":[["$","div",null,{"className":"eyebrow","children":"The solution"}],["$","h2",null,{"cla